     6	    floor(density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(density)
     7	
     8	clamped to ``[0, total_phrases]``. The deterministic floor guarantees a
     9	baseline density per mode while the Bernoulli term keeps neighbouring
    10	pieces from being identical. ``sampler_density`` is the scheduler's
    11	canonical "how often should ``sw_sampler`` appear?" weight, not a gain
    12	control: solitary=0.70, companion=0.25, working_ambience=0.10,
    13	evening_reflection=0.65, storm=0.45.
