 succeeded in 0ms:
   120	- **`sampler_dominating`** — fires per piece when the sampler accounts
   121	  for more than ~60% of total events (`SAMPLER_DOMINATING_RATIO_THRESHOLD`).
   122	  It opens at `severity="warning"` and escalates to `"fail"` after a
   123	  configurable consecutive-piece streak. Guards against the sampler
   124	  taking over the ensemble: the quintet discipline is "heavy sampler
   125	  use replaces, not adds."
   126	- **`sampler_silent_quintet_member`** — fires across a rolling
   127	  50-piece window when sampler usage drops below a mode-weighted
   128	  floor. The threshold scales with the active mode's `sampler_density`
   129	  reference, so `working_ambience` (density 0.1) does not trip it
   130	  while `solitary` (density 0.7) holds the full bar. Guards against
   131	  the sampler quietly disappearing from the quintet so that no one
   132	  notices the memory voice has gone silent for days.
   133	
   134	Both detectors take their identifiers verbatim from
   135	`render/antipatterns.py`; the doc regression test pins those names so
   136	a rename in code forces a doc update.
   137	
   138	## Mode Density Reference
   139	
   140	`sampler_density` is the canonical scheduling weight for `sw_sampler`.
   141	It does not mean gain, wetness, or prominence in the mix. It tells the
   142	composer and diagnostics how much of a piece's phrase grid the memory
   143	voice should occupy on average. CCS-023 turns it into
   144	`floor(density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(density)` scheduled sampler
   145	events, and CCS-030 uses the same value as the reference weight for the
   146	rolling "silent quintet member" detector.
   147	
   148	| Mode | `sampler_density` | Scheduling intent |
   149	| --- | --- | --- |
   150	| `solitary` | `0.70` | Heavy memory-voice presence; the room can listen back to itself often. |
   151	| `companion` | `0.25` | Light sampler participation; memory colors the piece without taking over. |
   152	| `working_ambience` | `0.10` | Minimal sampler usage so focused work stays undisturbed. |
   153	| `evening_reflection` | `0.65` | Frequent sampler entries during the most reflective, risk-tolerant mode. |
   154	| `storm` | `0.45` | Moderate-heavy sampler use to add pressure without dominating the ensemble. |
   155	
   156	## Integration Points
   157	
   158	The sampler does not run in isolation. These are the seams where it
   159	plugs into the rest of CypherClaw.
   160	
   161	- **Identity layer — `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py`.**
   162	  Owns `SIGNATURE_VOICES`, the per-mode `sampler_density`, and the
   163	  `VOICE_ROLES` map. The quintet target is documented in the
   164	  musicianship roadmap; the file itself is on the pending list (see
   165	  Status). The capture daemon also calls `bootstrap_identity()` from
   166	  `src/cypherclaw/first_boot.py` during `main()` so a first boot mints
   167	  and persists an `InstanceIdentity` before any JACK connection or
   168	  capture write happens.
   169	- **Cast planner — `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py`.**
   170	  `select_cast_ids` takes `preferred_synths` and `voice_count_target`;
   171	  the sampler joins the cast through this same path. Once
   172	  `SampleSelector` lands, a `SampleRecord` will be attached to sampler
   173	  cast entries at commission time so the dispatcher does not have to
   174	  re-pick.
   175	- **Mix engine — `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py` and
   176	  `mix_engine.py`.** Defines the `sampler_bus` mix slot, its peak-
   177	  normalized gain staging, and the gentler `compression_ratio = 1.5`
   178	  used to preserve grain transients. The `sw_master_smooth` SynthDef
   179	  exposes `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` controls so live
   180	  rebalancing does not require restarting scsynth.

